postcontent: Daisy SOFT Air pistol-NOT airsoft.  There's a big difference.  Google it. Soft air guns were made for a short time- 1 1/2 years, 1986-87.  Its said they were discontinued because they were too realistic looking.  This one is modeled after the Smith & Wesson Model 59 9mm semi auto.  It functions very similiar-plastic bb's are inserted into the "cartridge" which are then loaded into the double stack magazine.  That loads into the pistol, when the trigger is pulled, the slide moves rearward, when you push it forward, it strips a "cartridge" from the magazie and cocks the spring.  When the trigger is pulled, the "cartridge" fires and the cycle starts over until the magazie is empty.
